# Transient runtime state written by bin/launch-team.sh and bin/stop-team.sh:
# per-role launch prompts and the active-team record (pids, tmux windows).
# `.team/` is the legacy single-team mode; `.team-<run-id>/` is the per-run mode
# (TEAM_RUN_ID set), so both patterns are ignored.
.team/
.team-*/
# state-backup cron log (runtime artifact; the .team-*/ dir glob above does not match a bare file)
.team-backup.log

# Per-clone target config written by bin/run.sh (local, not for the template).
project.conf

# Generated team tmux config (per-clone, imports your prefix; not for the template).
team.tmux.conf

# Privacy: per-project goal/task briefs are private working files. A real brief
# can carry endpoints, emails, local paths, and app internals, none of which
# belong in this public template. Only the templates and the curated generic
# demos are tracked; everything else under goals/ and tasks/ is ignored, so a
# stray `git add .` cannot leak a real project brief.
goals/*
!goals/_TEMPLATE.md
!goals/bugfix-inflection.md
!goals/bugfix-slugify.md
!goals/bugfix-validatorjs.md
!goals/csv-dashboard.md
!goals/expense-tracker.md
!goals/repo-bugfix.md

tasks/*
!tasks/_TEMPLATE.md

# Past-run task artifacts are private working history; not shipped.
tasks-archive/

# Personal infra tooling, hardcoded to a private deployment (resource names,
# regions, alarm/metric names). Kept local, not shipped with the template.
bin/preflight-cutover-observation.sh

# Operator's working notes for resuming a paused run. Personal to one run id;
# not part of the template.
RESUME-HERE.md
